{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The appellant apparently makes no claim that the lease is valid for the full term, but insists that he is entitled to the possession of the premises for the year 1919, because in September of 1918 he sowed 320 acres of wheat upon the premises. This wheat was sown after appellant had notice that he would be required to vacate at the termination of the first year. This court in a number of cases has held that an unacknowledged lease of community property is good only for one year. In 
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I27f50c94f7e611d983e7e9deff98dc6f&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ea419c1c2e8e4ee19b2740f47a63fcc2&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1917002086&pubNum=660&originatingDoc=Icc0564a5f88311d99439b076ef9ec4de&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul1 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Spreitzer v. Miller, 98 Wash. 601, 168 Pac. 179,
}}}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 a number of cases so holding are cited, and we there said:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa400 \sb400 
\u8216\'3fHence it has consistently been held that a contract to lease community land, made by a married man without his wife joining him in the manner provided by the last-quoted section, the lessee knowing of its community character, is clearly in contravention thereof.\u8217\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb200 
It follows, from what we said in that case, that the lease in this case was valid only for the year 1918.
\par 
}
}
}
