 In that case Judge Parker, speaking for the court, said:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8216\'3fThis is not a case of giving a statutory notice to quit, looking to the termination of a tenancy, but it is a case of preventing the commencement of a new tenancy, or rather of preventing 
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_660_883_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_660_883_1}
