{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 this court said upon the question of estoppel:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li800 
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8216\'3fTo make an oral lease good for one year under the theory of estoppel, there must be some element of benefit to the landlord aside from the rent reserved, or some injustice to the tenant that a court of equity will not tolerate, as, for instance, where the landlord has 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_799_259_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_799_259_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*259
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa400 \sb400 
 made the lease conditioned upon some alteration or improvement that would enhance the value of the property, or where the value of the property lies in the taking of an annual crop. In other words, the mere possession, the payment of rent, and the conduct of a business in the usual way and for the sole benefit of the tenant, unaccompanied by circumstances which will create a consideration going to the term, will not make an oral lease from month to month a term lease, resting in estoppel.\u8217\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
